In Hong Kong, a two-year-old boy recovered from bird flu, while a three-year-old boy and a man died from the H5N1 strain.
A 13-year-old girl is currently hospitalized.
Hospitals in Hong Kong are testing all patients for the flu, with relatives also showing symptoms.
Macao residents are urged not to panic as no cases have been reported there.
Chicken sales have dropped, but experts assure the safety of imported poultry.
Hong Kong and Macao are coordinating efforts to prevent the spread of the virus.
Tourists are reassured that the situation is under control, with strict measures in place to prevent an outbreak.
